Lawyer Ahmednassir Abdullahi, who is also known as Grand Mullah, has left many Kenyans green with envy after photos of his brand new German machine surfaced online.Abdullahi, who is one of the sharpest legal minds in Kenya and a senior counsel, has added a Mercedes Benz AMG G63 to his collection.For those not in the know, the swanky ride the city lawyer has just bought costs $140,825 or Sh14 million before tax. The figure could go as high as Sh20 million after duties.The car can accelerate from 0-100 Km/h in 5.4 seconds. The G63 uses a twin-turbocharged 5.5-liter V8 engine that makes 563 horsepower at 5,500 rpm.